name: Oddbird Domaine de la Prade Merlot Shiraz - Red Wine - Non-Alcoholic - 0%
description: Oddbird Domaine De La Prade Organic is a non-alcoholic red wine. It is made from a blend of Merlot and Shiraz from the Languedoc-Roussillon region of France. Aged for 12 months, this wine has notes of blackberry, cherry, plum and caramel. Oddbird is on a mission to transform society’s drinking culture by creating world-class beverages – liberated from alcohol. Founded by Moa Gürbüzer, a decades-long therapist/social worker, Oddbird has grown into Sweden’s largest producer of quality wines. 700ml/0%Alc

name: Eisberg Sauvignon Blanc Non Alcoholic
description: Made from de alcoholised Sauvignon Blanc grapes with classic gooseberry and tropical fruit flavours. 750ml

name: Heineken 0.0 6x330ml can
description: Heineken’s unique 0.0 recipe is brewed with pure malt and special A-Yeast, just like the original Heineken lager beer. Heineken 0.0, a natural, pure malt lager for a premium taste, without alcohol. 6x330ml can

name: Kopparberg Strawberry & Lime Non Alcoholic
description: The experienced cider makers at Kopparberg have put their efforts into going alcohol free and have been rewarded with this fantastic strawberry & lime Cider. Raspberry and blackcurrant flavours burst from this cider giving it a rich and indulgent energy. It’s the perfect fruity refreshment for any occasion. 500ml Bottle

name: Erdinger Alkoholfrei 500ml
description: Erdinger Alkoholfrei is brewed under the strict Bavarian Purity Law, which means it is made from only high quality, natural ingredients. The isotonic thirst quencher with the inimitable refreshing taste provides the body with essential nutrients. Folic acid and vitamin B12 reduce fatigue and support the immune system, B12 also promotes energy-yielding metabolism. Just one bottle (0.5l) per day contributes to a healthy nutrition. Erdinger Alkoholfrei contains less than 0.5% vol. alc.

name: Domaine De La Prade Chardonnay
description: A crispy 100% Chardonnay wine from the Languedoc-Roussillon region of France. The Domaine de la Prade Chardonnay combines fresh tones of citrus and apple with a touch of pear and a round butteriness. Domaine de la Prade Chardonnay is matured for 12 months before being gently liberated from alcohol. Alc 0.0%, 750ml.

name: Maisels Weisse Non Alcoholic Bottle
description: Maisel’s Weisse “Alkoholfrei” is a deep amber in colour and is jam packed with fruity banana flavours. Its balanced flavour and creamy taste make it very easy to drink. 500ml bottle

name: Eisberg Cabernet Sauvignon Non Alcoholic
description: A rich premium non alcoholic red wine with a deep ruby colour and an aroma of cherries & plums, this wine goes brilliantly with lamb or beef. 750ml

name: Eins Zwei Riesling Non Alcoholic
description: Clean and fresh with notes of lime and citrus; surprisingly rhubarb and a little hint of red apples on an underlying mineral base. The finish is dry and long. Extremely close to the depth, structure and weight of a normal wine.0% Alc..750ml

name: Kopparberg Mixed Fruit Non alcoholic
description: The experienced cider makers at Kopparberg have put their efforts into going alcohol free and have been rewarded with this fantastic Mixed Fruits Cider. Raspberry and blackcurrant flavours burst from this cider giving it a rich and indulgent energy. It’s the perfect fruity refreshment for any occasion. 500ml Bottle

name: Nosecco Alcohol Free Prosecco
description: Nosecco is a non alcoholic sparkling alternative to Prosecco that looks just like any other bottle of fizz. Once in the glass it has a similar pale golden colour and the same fizz consistencies that you would expect in a sparkling wine. It is slightly sweeter than the average, but definitely a great party starter. 750ml bottle

name: Leitz Zero Point Five Alcohol Free Cabernet Sauvignon
description: The Leitz zero alcohol cabernet sauvignon offers hints of ripe cassis and berry flavours as well as dark cherry flavour and aromas of black cherries, blueberries and chocolate with soft tannins and a dry finish. Research has proven the antioxidant and cholesterol fighting effects of drinking red wine, and the Leitz cabernet sauvignon offers these with the added benefit of zero alcohol. 0% Alc/750ml.

name: Peroni Non Alcoholic 4x330ml bottle
description: Zero Alcohol, Pure Style. Peroni Libera 0.0% is a light-bodied non-alcohol alternative for those who want to live their week fully without compromise. Peroni Libera 0.0% offers a refreshing and crisp taste with a fine bitterness and a fast and clean finish. 4x330ml bottle

name: Eins Zwei Zero Sparkling Riesling Non Alcohol
description: Eins Zwei Zero is an impressively moreish alcohol-free Sparkling Riesling, with flavours of citrus and rhubarb and an aromatic touch of lime. To remove the alcohol from the wine, a gentle vacuum distillation has been used in order to preserve the natural Riesling flavours. This modern technique has been chosen because it allows the extraction of alcohol under extremely low pressure and temperature (around 30°C). No flavour is lost through the treatment of the wine through the de-alcoholisation process. 0.0%/750ml

name: Stiegl Freibier Non Alcohol
description: Unfiltered and non-alcoholic. Stiegl-Freibier stands out through its full-bodied, balanced taste. Aromatic Austrian Saphir hops lend the unfiltered, nonalcoholic beer in a refreshing, lime-like taste. 0.0%Alc/500ml bottle.

name: Eisberg Chardonnay Non Alcoholic
description: Eisberg created this fresh, crisp Chardonnay just for you. It has hints of lemon, ripe peaches, and soft vanilla, and has had the alcohol carefully removed making it perfect for you to enjoy at any time. 750ml

name: Hollow Legs Non Alcohol Cabernet Sauvignon
description: Hollow Leg is an Irish-founded company specializing in high-quality, alcohol-free wines that offer a satisfying alternative to traditional alcoholic beverages. Collaborating with Galician winemaker Pablo Martinez, Dublin restaurateur Jamie O’Toole, and WineLab, they have developed a range of wines that preserve the mouthfeel, taste, and aroma of premium grapes without the need for added sugars or artificial additives. Their offerings include Albariño, Cabernet Sauvignon, Sparkling White Cuvée, and Sparkling Rosé, each crafted to provide a refreshing and enjoyable experience. Notably, each 150ml glass contains only 0.4g of sugar and 9 calories, making them a mindful choice for those seeking to reduce alcohol consumption without compromising on taste.

name: Non Alcohol Nozeco Still Chardonnay
description: Its crystal colour with golden reflections, its expressive and charming nose, mixing perfumes of white flowers, citrus fruits and yellow fruits will charm you. With its subtle hints of citrus fruit and floral aroma, this very refreshing Nozeco Still White will perfectly pair with a lovely aperitif or dessert.

name: Lervig No Worries Non Alcohol Craft Beer
description: Need a worry free alcohol free beer? We got it for you. A lightly hopped and pleasantly refreshing pale ale, fermented with a brewers yeast which cant ferment Maltose. Tasting like a low abv beer due to this process you can enjoy the beer without the effect. 0.5% ALC/330ml can.

name: Eisberg Sparkling Rose Non Alcoholic
description: Celebrate with great sparkling wine without the alcohol, meaning you can drive home safely and wake up feeling fresh and ready to go.

name: Lucky Saint
description: Superior Unfiltered Lager. A classic lager made with four natural ingredients – Pilsner Malt, Hallertau Hops, spring water and classic lager yeast. Vegan, 53 Calories Per Lager, 0.5% ABV
